  "text": "In work published online around the time of the workshop [CITATION_1] , Tchesnokov et al. [CITATION_2] assessed the inhibitory activity of CF2648, the monophosphorylated prodrug of acyclovir, against HIV-1 in MT4 cells. The mean ±sd 50% effective concentration of CF2648 rose from 3.4 ±2.8 µM against wild-type virus to 51 ±2.3 µM against V75I, a 15-fold increase.",
